{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1596,"text":"Here are two reasons companies fail:"},{"time":5208,"text":"they only do more of the same,"},{"time":8478,"text":"or they only do what's new."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11613,"text":"To me the real, real\nsolution to quality growth"},{"time":16537,"text":"is figuring out the balance\nbetween two activities:"},{"time":20126,"text":"exploration and exploitation."},{"time":23114,"text":"Both are necessary,"},{"time":24728,"text":"but it can be too much of a good thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29154,"text":"Consider Facit."},{"time":31061,"text":"I'm actually old enough to remember them."},{"time":33489,"text":"Facit was a fantastic company."},{"time":35999,"text":"They were born deep in the Swedish forest,"},{"time":38496,"text":"and they made the best\nmechanical calculators in the world."},{"time":42524,"text":"Everybody used them."},{"time":44798,"text":"And what did Facit do when\nthe electronic calculator came along?"},{"time":49691,"text":"They continued doing exactly the same."},{"time":52953,"text":"In six months, they went\nfrom maximum revenue ..."},{"time":56695,"text":"and they were gone."},{"time":58649,"text":"Gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59824,"text":"To me, the irony about the Facit story"},{"time":63720,"text":"is hearing about the Facit engineers,"},{"time":67010,"text":"who had bought cheap, small\nelectronic calculators in Japan"},{"time":72117,"text":"that they used to double-check\ntheir calculators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75802,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77239,"text":"Facit did too much exploitation."},{"time":80422,"text":"But exploration can go wild, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82900,"text":"A few years back,"},{"time":84075,"text":"I worked closely alongside\na European biotech company."},{"time":88447,"text":"Let's call them OncoSearch."},{"time":90830,"text":"The company was brilliant."},{"time":92511,"text":"They had applications that promised\nto diagnose, even cure,"},{"time":97153,"text":"certain forms of blood cancer."},{"time":100190,"text":"Every day was about\ncreating something new."},{"time":103744,"text":"They were extremely innovative,"},{"time":106272,"text":"and the mantra was,\n\"When we only get it right,\""},{"time":109172,"text":"or even, \"We want it perfect.\""},{"time":112687,"text":"The sad thing is,"},{"time":114568,"text":"before they became perfect --"},{"time":116490,"text":"even good enough --"},{"time":118443,"text":"they became obsolete."},{"time":121331,"text":"OncoSearch did too much exploration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125602,"text":"I first heard about exploration\nand exploitation about 15 years ago,"},{"time":131381,"text":"when I worked as a visiting\nscholar at Stanford University."},{"time":135428,"text":"The founder of the idea is Jim March."},{"time":138168,"text":"And to me the power of the idea\nis its practicality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143168,"text":"Exploration."},{"time":144847,"text":"Exploration is about\ncoming up with what's new."},{"time":148772,"text":"It's about search,"},{"time":150027,"text":"it's about discovery,"},{"time":151494,"text":"it's about new products,"},{"time":153080,"text":"it's about new innovations."},{"time":155591,"text":"It's about changing our frontiers."},{"time":159408,"text":"Our heroes are people\nwho have done exploration:"},{"time":162867,"text":"Madame Curie,"},{"time":164232,"text":"Picasso,"},{"time":165414,"text":"Neil Armstrong,"},{"time":166612,"text":"Sir Edmund Hillary, etc."},{"time":169210,"text":"I come from Norway;"},{"time":171569,"text":"all our heroes are explorers,\nand they deserve to be."},{"time":177364,"text":"We all know that exploration is risky."},{"time":180454,"text":"We don't know the answers,"},{"time":182297,"text":"we don't know if we're going to find them,"},{"time":184392,"text":"and we know that the risks are high."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186693,"text":"Exploitation is the opposite."},{"time":188608,"text":"Exploitation is taking\nthe knowledge we have"},{"time":191709,"text":"and making good, better."},{"time":194344,"text":"Exploitation is about making\nour trains run on time."},{"time":197984,"text":"It's about making good products\nfaster and cheaper."},{"time":202900,"text":"Exploitation is not risky --"},{"time":205911,"text":"in the short term."},{"time":207595,"text":"But if we only exploit,"},{"time":209425,"text":"it's very risky in the long term."},{"time":212503,"text":"And I think we all have memories\nof the famous pop groups"},{"time":216285,"text":"who keep singing the same songs\nagain and again,"},{"time":219719,"text":"until they become obsolete\nor even pathetic."},{"time":224204,"text":"That's the risk of exploitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228667,"text":"So if we take a long-term\nperspective, we explore."},{"time":233427,"text":"If we take a short-term\nperspective, we exploit."},{"time":237693,"text":"Small children, they explore all day."},{"time":240880,"text":"All day it's about exploration."},{"time":243326,"text":"As we grow older,"},{"time":244763,"text":"we explore less because we have\nmore knowledge to exploit on."},{"time":249820,"text":"The same goes for companies."},{"time":252706,"text":"Companies become,\nby nature, less innovative"},{"time":256594,"text":"as they become more competent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259239,"text":"And this is, of course,\na big worry to CEOs."},{"time":263410,"text":"And I hear very often questions\nphrased in different ways."},{"time":267943,"text":"For example,"},{"time":269125,"text":"\"How can I both effectively run\nand reinvent my company?\""},{"time":274557,"text":"Or, \"How can I make sure"},{"time":276475,"text":"that our company changes\nbefore we become obsolete"},{"time":280860,"text":"or are hit by a crisis?\""},{"time":283584,"text":"So, doing one well is difficult."},{"time":286164,"text":"Doing both well as the same time is art --"},{"time":289955,"text":"pushing both exploration and exploitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293138,"text":"So one thing we've found"},{"time":294658,"text":"is only about two percent of companies\nare able to effectively explore"},{"time":301378,"text":"and exploit at the same time, in parallel."},{"time":305570,"text":"But when they do,"},{"time":307478,"text":"the payoffs are huge."},{"time":310337,"text":"So we have lots of great examples."},{"time":312750,"text":"We have Nestl√© creating Nespresso,"},{"time":315490,"text":"we have Lego going into animated films,"},{"time":318536,"text":"Toyota creating the hybrids,"},{"time":320966,"text":"Unilever pushing into sustainability --"},{"time":323461,"text":"there are lots of examples,\nand the benefits are huge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327812,"text":"Why is balancing so difficult?"},{"time":330846,"text":"I think it's difficult\nbecause there are so many traps"},{"time":333500,"text":"that keep us where we are."},{"time":335975,"text":"So I'll talk about two,\nbut there are many."}]},{"cues":[{"time":339098,"text":"So let's talk about\nthe perpetual search trap."},{"time":342616,"text":"We discover something,"},{"time":344452,"text":"but we don't have the patience\nor the persistence"},{"time":347331,"text":"to get at it and make it work."},{"time":349683,"text":"So instead of staying with it,\nwe create something new."},{"time":352852,"text":"But the same goes for that,"},{"time":354176,"text":"then we're in the vicious circle"},{"time":355951,"text":"of actually coming up with ideas\nbut being frustrated."},{"time":360381,"text":"OncoSearch was a good example."},{"time":362725,"text":"A famous example is, of course, Xerox."},{"time":366607,"text":"But we don't only see this in companies."},{"time":368731,"text":"We see this in the public sector as well."},{"time":371726,"text":"We all know that any kind\nof effective reform of education,"},{"time":377472,"text":"research, health care, even defense,"},{"time":379923,"text":"takes 10, 15, maybe 20 years to work."},{"time":383766,"text":"But still, we change much more often."},{"time":387090,"text":"We really don't give them the chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390424,"text":"Another trap is the success trap."},{"time":394808,"text":"Facit fell into the success trap."},{"time":398275,"text":"They literally held\nthe future in their hands,"},{"time":401549,"text":"but they couldn't see it."},{"time":402787,"text":"They were simply so good\nat making what they loved doing,"},{"time":406566,"text":"that they wouldn't change."},{"time":409187,"text":"We are like that, too."},{"time":410504,"text":"When we know something well,\nit's difficult to change."},{"time":414872,"text":"Bill Gates has said:"},{"time":417016,"text":"\"Success is a lousy teacher."},{"time":420040,"text":"It seduces us into thinking\nwe cannot fail.\""},{"time":424457,"text":"That's the challenge with success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":427886,"text":"So I think there are some lessons,\nand I think they apply to us."},{"time":431364,"text":"And they apply to our companies."},{"time":433570,"text":"The first lesson is:\nget ahead of the crisis."},{"time":437949,"text":"And any company that's able to innovate"},{"time":440542,"text":"is actually able to also buy\nan insurance in the future."},{"time":444709,"text":"Netflix -- they could so easily\nhave been content"},{"time":447596,"text":"with earlier generations of distribution,"},{"time":450484,"text":"but they always -- and I think\nthey will always --"},{"time":453065,"text":"keep pushing for the next battle."},{"time":455572,"text":"I see other companies that say,"},{"time":457961,"text":"\"I'll win the next innovation cycle,\nwhatever it takes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":463635,"text":"Second one: think in multiple time scales."},{"time":466918,"text":"I'll share a chart with you,"},{"time":468280,"text":"and I think it's a wonderful one."},{"time":470461,"text":"Any company we look at,"},{"time":472198,"text":"taking a one-year perspective"},{"time":474021,"text":"and looking at the valuation\nof the company,"},{"time":476322,"text":"innovation typically accounts\nfor only about 30 percent."},{"time":480187,"text":"So when we think one year,"},{"time":481598,"text":"innovation isn't really that important."},{"time":484490,"text":"Move ahead, take a 10-year perspective\non the same company --"},{"time":488082,"text":"suddenly, innovation and ability\nto renew account for 70 percent."},{"time":494253,"text":"But companies can't choose."},{"time":495754,"text":"They need to fund the journey\nand lead the long term."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500746,"text":"Third:"},{"time":502304,"text":"invite talent."},{"time":503974,"text":"I don't think it's possible for any of us"},{"time":506546,"text":"to be able to balance exploration\nand exploitation by ourselves."},{"time":511100,"text":"I think it's a team sport."},{"time":512830,"text":"I think we need to allow challenging."},{"time":516273,"text":"I think the mark of a great company\nis being open to be challenged,"},{"time":521187,"text":"and the mark of a good corporate board\nis to constructively challenge."},{"time":526264,"text":"I think that's also what\ngood parenting is about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530858,"text":"Last one: be skeptical of success."},{"time":534133,"text":"Maybe it's useful to think back\nat the old triumph marches in Rome,"},{"time":540490,"text":"when the generals, after a big victory,"},{"time":544010,"text":"were given their celebration."},{"time":546754,"text":"Riding into Rome on the carriage,"},{"time":549513,"text":"they always had a companion\nwhispering in their ear,"},{"time":553759,"text":"\"Remember, you're only human.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":557923,"text":"So I hope I made the point:"},{"time":560701,"text":"balancing exploration and exploitation"},{"time":563747,"text":"has a huge payoff."},{"time":565218,"text":"But it's difficult,\nand we need to be conscious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568338,"text":"I want to just point out two questions\nthat I think are useful."},{"time":573397,"text":"First question is,\nlooking at your own company:"},{"time":577446,"text":"In which areas do you see\nthat the company is at the risk"},{"time":581780,"text":"of falling into success traps,"},{"time":584048,"text":"of just going on autopilot?"},{"time":587105,"text":"And what can you do to challenge?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":591639,"text":"Second question is:"},{"time":594530,"text":"When did I explore something new last,"},{"time":597815,"text":"and what kind of effect did it have on me?"},{"time":600814,"text":"Is that something I should do more of?"},{"time":603596,"text":"In my case, yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606657,"text":"So let me leave you with this."},{"time":608692,"text":"Whether you're an explorer by nature"},{"time":611997,"text":"or whether you tend to exploit\nwhat you already know,"},{"time":615923,"text":"don't forget: the beauty\nis in the balance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621392,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622576,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}